	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f101888817151906">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=5138&amp;mid=101888817151906">Just a thought...</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=5138&amp;mid=101888817151906#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 15th 12:35 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=148957"><span id=" ">tholosfrostreaver</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">26 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.80]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hi just your averave shaman with a few thoughts about all this arguing<br/><br/>I see valid points for why each ring as useful. I carry different equipment for different situations. The most important thing to consider is that everyone has different equipment and is a different level. This is all about Min/Maxing your stats, to your level, and how you play the game. There are many factors that can make one item more appealing then another.<br/><br/>At higher levels you wont need dex or str with your rings anyways. A 49+ shaman can buff you 134 str and 100 dex,(note this could change, b/c of a HoS buffing bug, lets hope it doesn't) This should max out your str and dex ability no problem. Agi is harder to max out even with buffs so that may be your logic to go with this ring.<br/><br/>If you dont have a shaman to buff you, you might switch these with the fire emerald rings with 6 str and dex. My rogue would where these to max out BS ability. Warrior might to get better strength bonus and procs. <br/><br/>If you are a mid level player (20-40) you might not have your abilities maxed or may only have one maxed (str in my opinion is easiest ability to max). If your strenght is maxed then this might be a better ring for you.<br/><br/>If you are the main tank or the backup that keeps adds off the casters, HP AC rings will most likely be your ring of choice. If you are not a Main tank you really dont need AC or HP, because theoretically you wont be getting hit. <br/><br/>Agility is rumored to effect your ability to dodge or evade getting hit. AC is supposed to reduce the amount of damage you will recieve from each blow. If this is true then if you get quick agro (ie from proc or BS) you want to dodge the blow and not take any damage. As you will only have agro for a brief moment. But main tank will be taking a continual beating ie they want ac to weaken the hits and more hp to take more hits.<br/><br/>I like this ring and want at least one to have in my arsenal of equipment for my ranger, rogue, shaman, and warrior. Just remember what people choose to equip is to mim/max thier individual character There is no one right answer. I hope this will help some people out.<br/><br/>You may now flame me for any spelling or info errors, or because you hate kats and frogs...<br/><br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Apr 15 12:33:12 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />one day Ill be uber...&nbsp;&nbsp;one day...<br/><br/>Tholos Frostreaver<br/>50 Barbarian Shaman<br/>7th Hammer</td></tr>
